x4freetext: Large-aperture collimator (8 cm diam.) used to make
beam profile flat over the surface of the samples.
Energy resolution of better than 1% at En=100 MeV,
Weighted average of data sets from four setups (FIC,
PPAC perpendicular, PPAC tilted 1 and 2) in Table IV
Same as Table IV of Phys.Rev.C91(2015)024602

x4code.actHelp: Data received at the data center

x4freetext: On. Data received from Carlos Paradela.
Two different measurements were performed with
Diam. of 8 cm (FIC1) or 5 cm (FIC2), isotopic purity
of better than 99%, non-uniformity of 5 to 10 %.
Due to the large uncertainty of 238U mass of FIC2
(larger than 3%), the FIC2 data set was normalized to
the FIC1 data set in the 1 to 10 MeV neutron energy
Efficiency (only to FIC1) and dead-time corrections
